This paper focuses on policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of linear function approximation and convex-concave saddle point problems suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of numerical experiments and benchmark problems suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
